# The while Loop

A `while` loop repeats a block of code as long as a condition is true.

```php
while (condition) {
    // code to repeat
}
```

Before each iteration, the condition is checked. If true, the block runs. If false, the loop ends.

```php
<?php
$count = 1;
while ($count <= 5) {
    echo "Count: $count\n";
    $count++;
}
?>
```
Output:
Count: 1
Count: 2
Count: 3
Count: 4
Count: 5

## Never Ending Story

If the condition never becomes false, the loop runs forever (infinite loop). This will crash your script.

```php
// Infinite loop – missing increment
$i = 1;
while ($i <= 5) {
    echo $i;
    // forgot $i++
}
```

Always ensure the condition will eventually become false.

